        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:24PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1224 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marshall, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albion...              Marshall...            Marengo...
Ceresco...             Duck Lake...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
